:INFO
What Makes a Grow Light Actually Work
Plants use light in the red (630 to 680 nm) and blue (430 to 470 nm) spectrum \
bands most efficiently for photosynthesis. Full-spectrum white LEDs that include \
both ends work well for most home growers and are easier to source than dedicated \
red/blue panels. The metric that matters most is PPFD (photosynthetic photon \
flux density), measured in micromoles per square meter per second. Leafy herbs \
want 200 to 400 PPFD. Fruiting plants want 400 to 600 PPFD. Distance from the \
canopy is the easiest way to adjust PPFD without changing hardware.

:COUNTER.half
200 to 400 PPFD
Target for leafy greens and herbs
