|
:INFO
Wire the Strips and Driver
Wire LED strips in series or parallel according to the driver's voltage and current \
specs. A meanwell HLG driver has a dimmer potentiometer on the side: use it to set \
output current and thus brightness. Solder connections or use wago connectors rated for

:PATH
Mount and Dial In Height
Hang the panel on adjustable rope ratchets so you can raise it as plants grow.
|
:INFO
Mount and Dial In Height
Hang the panel on adjustable rope ratchets so you can raise it as plants grow. Start at \
24 inches above seedlings and lower to 12 to 18 inches for mature herbs. Use a light \
meter app or a dedicated PAR meter to check PPFD at canopy level. Run the light

:CHECKLIST
Before First Power-On
[ ] All solder joints or wago connectors checked for shorts
[ ] Driver voltage and current set to match LED strip spec
[ ] Thermal adhesive tape seated firmly between strips and aluminum
[ ] Rope ratchets rated for panel weight and mounted to a solid anchor
[ ] Timer programmed and tested without plants underneath

